Image:Ledger-sm2.jpg|<center>[[Kiowa]] ledger art, possibly of the 1874 Buffalo Wallow battle, [[Red River War]].
</gallery>

====Plateau====

Since the archaic period the Plateau region, also known as the [[Intermontane|Intermontaine]], had been a center of trade. Plateau people lived subsistence lifestyles and were primarily nomadic.<ref>Berlo and Phillips, 131</ref> Because of this, their art derived its form and style from other regions <U+2013> the Northwest coast and the Plains in particular <U+2013> except in basketry and weaving, which were the most varied and developed art forms. The [[Nez Perce]], the [[Yakama]], and other cultures weave corn husks or [[hemp dogbane]] into bags, which are decorated with "bold, geometric designs".<ref>Berlo and Phillips, 132</ref>

<gallery widths="170px" heights="180px" perrow="4">
