</gallery>

====Great Basin and California====

The [[Great Basin]] and California also have a tradition of basket-making. In the late nineteenth century Washoe baskets became a popular commodity for tourists in the southern California, which resulted in great innovation in the form of the baskets.<ref>Berlo and Phillips, 136</ref>  

<gallery widths="175px" heights="180px" perrow="4">
